name: Yakima County Health District COVID Vaccination Site
info: ***1st DOSE PFIZER VACCINATIONS!!!!***!!!!VACUNAS DE PRIMERA DOSIS PFIZER!!! The vaccination clinic will take place at YMCA in Yakima. Masks are required. Please wear clothing which allows access to your shoulder. Vaccinations at this site are reserved for people who live and/or work in Washington State. All individuals 12 and over are eligible to get vaccinated. Those under 18 must be accompanied by a parent/guardian or must get parental consent via video/phone call or paper format. La clínica de vacunación se llevará acabo en el YMCA de Yakima. Se requieren máscaras. Por favor, use ropa que permita acceso a su brazo. Las vacunas en este sitio están reservadas para las personas que viven o trabajan en el estado de Washington. Todas las personas mayores de 12 años son elegibles para vacunarse. Los menores de 18 años deben estar acompañados por un padre/tutor o deben obtener el consentimiento de los padres por video/llamada telefónica o en papel. ***1st DOSE PFIZER VACCINATIONS!!!!***!!!!VACUNAS DE PRIMERA DOSIS PFIZER!!!
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Thurston County Public Health Medical Reserve Corp
address: Tumwater High School - 700 Israel Road SW, Tumwater WA, 98501
info:
This is a Pfizer vaccination event for anyone age 12 and older. 

This is a walk-in clinic at Tumwater High School located at 700 Israel Road SW, Tumwater, WA 98501 from 12pm - 4pm. • All minors 12 to 17 years old must receive parent or guardian consent to receive a COVID-19 vaccine. This must be done in PrepMod when registering for an appointment. Parents or guardians do not have to be present at the time of vaccination if they signed the consent form online during registration. • Please bring a form of identification with you to your appointment - ID card, passport, or other document with your name and birthday on it. • Wear a short-sleeved shirt, but dress with layers if necessary. • Waiting at least 15 minutes after vaccination is required.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
